Challenge - 8
1. Go through all the 11 examples offered by Shiny package
2. Pick one among them of your choice and customize it
3. The customizations could be with text, images, plots, etc.
4. Insert screenshots of your final dashboard and explain your customizations in an R Markdown document
5. Knit the document and upload it on Canvas
6. Make sure that the corresponding code is saved in folder, "Week-8", upload it on Github.
7. Make sure that your Github profile is up-to-date with the coursework of all the Weeks so far.
The aim of this exercise is to familiarise you with the several possible ways Shiny can be used. 
```{r}
library(shiny)
runExample("01_hello")
```

